         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">24/8/61. ¶ Dear Dr Hooker ¶  ¶ Many many thanks for the noble collection of dried Indian plants, with which you enriched our Herbarium. They came in my book case, but half the books were destroyed by ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">61.08.24c</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-81, un-numbered letter after f. 48.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24/8/61.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Dr Hooker</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Many many thanks for the noble collection of dried Indian plants, with which you enriched our Herbarium. They came in my book case, but half the books were destroyed by Saltwater, but the plants miraculously escaped!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have pr Lincolnshire sent <name key="Azolla">Azolla</name> to Kew. <name key="Seringea">Seringea</name> &amp; <name key="Kerandrenia">Kerandrenia</name> may after all be kept distinct. My <name key="Seringea">Seringea</name>s are then <name key="Kerandrenia">Kerandrenia</name>s.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Accept my best congratulation to the V.P. of the L.S. and pray express to Mr Bentham my congratulation to his new high position.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham was elected President of the Linnean Society on 24 May 1861. J. Hooker was Vice-President.</p>
               </note> The copy of Prof Harveys Cape flora<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i.e. the first volume of Harvey &amp; Sonder (1859-65).</p>
               </note> arrived only within the last days. I am exceedingly obliged to him. His brother in law I see often.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to W. Hooker, 24 August 1861 (in this edition as 61-08-24a), n. 11.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have sent some seeds to Kew by my countryman, Dr Guenther, the Surgeon of the "Anglesey" recently gone out.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am glad Mr Bentham arrives at the same conclusion as myself respecting <name key="Macarthuria">Macarthuria</name>, upon which you find remarks by me nearly two years ago in the Fragmenta, referring it to <name key="Mollugineae">Mollugineae</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B60.02.02, p. 11; Bentham (1863-78) vol. 3, pp. 331-2.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Your truly</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>attached</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
